# WSL: Docker Desktop with native socket

On this machine:
- The native Ubuntu Docker daemon socket `/var/run/docker.sock` EXISTS and works
- The `default` context points to `unix:///var/run/docker.sock` and functions correctly
- Docker Desktop's `desktop-linux` context uses Windows-only `npipe://` transport and doesn't work from WSL

## Shell / CLI

- The `default` context works: `docker context use default && docker ps`
- Alternative: Use the WSL bind mount socket if needed: `export DOCKER_HOST=unix:///mnt/wsl/docker-desktop-bind-mounts/Ubuntu-22.04/docker.sock`
- Do NOT use `desktop-linux` context (it uses Windows-only `npipe://` transport)

## Harbor / oracle / NOP / verifier_health

- Scripts automatically detect and use the working socket via `scripts/harbor_docker_env.harbor_env()`
- The scripts prefer `/var/run/docker.sock` when available, falling back to WSL bind mount if needed
- Do not set `DOCKER_CONTEXT=desktop-linux` for gates

## Sandbox Note

Inside the sandbox, `/var/run/docker.sock` may not be visible due to filesystem restrictions. Harbor scripts handle this by detecting the available socket.
